<p><strong>Demons</strong>: these are sub-agents that come up in “hell realms” which are states of consciousness where you believe that you are a bad person and deserve some kind of punishment. The demons here are just, in my opinion, doing exactly what you expect them to do, namely, punishing you. I think that in addition to equanimity and metta, these entities also respond to boosting narratives of redemption that are wholesome in nature. For example, there is this spiritual belief that demons ultimately are all on the path towards God… they are just in a more extreme version of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parable_of_the_Prodigal_Son" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Parable of the Prodigal Son</a>, and they might take thousands of years to redeem themselves. But they will do so. In this case, you sending them metta and telling them that they are actually intrinsically good, can slowly, but surely, help them unwind their dissonant configurations.</p>



